<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3167&amp;p=22967#p22967</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3167&amp;p=22967#p22967"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Really cool idea.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3167&amp;p=22967#p22967"><![CDATA[
I think he wants to simulate *ANY* image as if it was being a game played on the NES. I don't think he cares for the composite artifacts or things like this.<br /><br />There could be a generic converter that took an image and attempted to modify it so that it could look like it was generated by a NES, but it would hardly look like a game actually being played.<br /><br />It will just look like a poor image conversion, with dithering, color bleed, and so on, things not usually present in an actual game.<br /><br />I think it may be funny to do manual convertions of screens from newer systems like the SNES or the Genesis/Mega Drive just to see how the games could have looked if they were made for the NES, but doing it automatically will just look like crap.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Fri Apr 06, 2007 11:26 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
